f=Cybersecurity/veil/operational/commands/veil-commands.md · h1:veil — Command Triggers=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · h1:veil — Command Triggers=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:veil — Command Triggers=\| "classify," "data classification," "what tier," "sensitivity label" \| data-classification \| /veil-classify \| · h1:veil — Command Triggers=\| "privacy," "DPIA," "data protection," "GDPR," "privacy by design" \| privacy-by-design \| /veil-privacy \| · h1:veil — Command Triggers=\| "DLP," "data loss," "exfiltration," "egress," "data leak" \| data-loss-prevention \| /veil-dlp \| · h1:veil — Command Triggers=\| "breach notification," "GDPR 72h," "notify regulator," "PIPEDA" \| breach-notification \| /veil-notify \| · h2:Precedence=**Classification first.** Before DLP monitoring breach notification, data classified. Unclassified data gets default INTERNAL treatment. **DLP alert confirmed exfiltration** breach-notification (check clocks). DLP confirms leak; breach-notification handles regulatory obligation. **Any notification** operator/legal approval required before sending. veil drafts; operator approves sends. **All gaps** (unclassified data, DLP blind spots, unclear jurisdictions) warden's register.